title: ‘Too many guns’: Firearms total over one million in NSW alone
description: Sky News host Paul Murray says there are “too many guns” in Australia following the Bondi Beach massacre.

title: ‘True leader’: Josh Frydenberg stands up for Jewish Australians
description: GXO Strategies Director Cameron Milner discusses the possibility of former treasurer Josh Frydenberg running for parliament in the 2028 election.  “Don’t we have a prime minister, someone in the making. Josh Frydenberg stood up," Mr Milner said.  “He stood up as a true leader today.  “Anthony Albanese hid in the shadows.”

title: Josh Frydenberg delivered ‘one of the defining political speeches of our era’: James Paterson
description: Shadow Finance Minister James Paterson claims Josh Frydenberg’s speech at Bondi Beach was an “electric performance”.  “We would love to have him back, I’ve missed him dearly,” Mr Paterson told Sky News host Sharri Markson.  “If he wants to run again, he would be enthusiastically embraced by his former colleagues.”

title: ‘Finished’: Albanese’s reputation destroyed after failing to attend Bondi massacre funerals
description: Sky News host Andrew Bolt says Anthony Albanese is “finished as prime minister” after his failure to support the Jewish community.  Mr Bolt said it was “devastating for his reputation” to not attend the first of the funerals for the victims of the Bondi massacre.  “Albanese is so diminished and so scared of the righteous fury of Jews and others over his extraordinary failure to confront our lethal Jew hatred.”

title: ‘The truth’: Albanese avoids the media over Bondi massacre
description: Sky News host Paul Murray says it is time to tell Australians “the truth” around Prime Minister Anthony Albanese avoiding confrontation around the Bondi massacre.

title: ‘Australia is leaderless’: Former treasurer outlines plan to address antisemitism
description: Former treasurer Josh Frydenberg analyses his roadmap for Australian leadership to follow.  “Australia is leaderless at the moment,” Mr Frydenberg told Sky News host Sharri Markson.  “What has taken place here needed a prime minister to stand up, accept responsibility and to say he would not waste a second before implementing the changes that were necessary … to ensure we don’t revisit another terrorist attack like this.”

title: ‘Stained our nation forever’: Bondi warning signs were there for ‘everyone to see’
description: Former treasurer Josh Frydenberg says the Bondi Beach massacre was a failure of Australian leadership.  “This was a complete failure,” Mr Frydenberg told Sky News host Sharri Markson.  “To root out this radical Islamist ideology that has taken hold in Australia.”

title: ‘Until you stand here’: Josh Frydenberg’s intense Bondi speech lauded
description: Sky News host Paul Murray highlights former treasurer Josh Frydenberg’s speech about Prime Minister Anthony Albanese in Bondi.

title: ‘Spending addiction’: Jim Chalmers exposed for govt ‘debt and deficit’
description: Sky News host Peta Credlin exposes Jim Chalmers boasting about the 2025-26 MYEFO, saying Labor’s problem is “addiction to spending.”  “Chalmers boasted that this was some sort of economic wizardry,” Ms Credlin said.  “The reality is, is that there’s still debt and deficit as far as the eye can see.”

title: 'Amazing speech': Sussan Ley ‘standing with’ Jewish people
description: Sky News host Sharri Markson claims Sussan Ley gave an “amazing speech” today.  “Sussan Ley was here tonight, she gave an amazing speech,” Ms Markson told Sky News host Paul Murray.  “Fire I haven’t seen from her before, she’s standing with us.”

title: ‘Sussex shock return’: Meghan Markle lays out demands for possible UK comeback
description: UK barrister and broadcaster Andrew Eborn reacts to Meghan Markle’s list of demands for a potential return to the UK.   “The Sussex shock return of the madness from Montecito,” Mr Eborn told Sky News Digital Presenter Gabriella Power.  “What it basically means is mending ties with King Charles and resolving Prince Harry’s security issues.  “Harry’s made it very clear he wants to get closer to his father … and this is a good stage, but what they’re saying is it comes with a Netflix package.  “It is about that security, it is about making sure that she gets that sort of respect and respect for all people in that conversation.”

title: Trump chief of staff slams Vanity Fair for misleading article
description: RNC Youth Advisory Council Co-Chair CJ Pearson analyses how United States President Donald Trump’s Chief of Staff Susie Wiles slammed Vanity Fair.  Ms Wiles said Vanity Fair wrote a disingenuously framed ‘hit piece’.  She also said significant context was ‘disregarded’.

title: ‘Deceptive and inflammatory’: Trump sues BBC for $5 billion over edited speech
description: Sky News host Rita Panahi highlights how United States President Donald Trump has finally sued the BBC.  Mr Trump officially sued for $5 billion.  He described the editing of his speech as ‘deceptive’ and ‘inflammatory’.

title: ‘Absolutely despicable’: Sarah Ferguson blasted for ‘offensive’ question to Josh Frydenberg
description: Sky News host Paul Murray claims ABC host Sarah Ferguson’s question to Josh Frydenberg was “disgraceful.”  “She immediately started to backpedal,” Mr Murray said.  “To end like that, that was the plan.”

title: Jewish bakery shuts down after Bondi attack
description: Avner’s Owner Ed Halmagyi has decided to shut down his bakery after the massacre of Jewish Australians in Bondi.
